<subSubSection pageId="774" pageNumber="775" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="774" pageNumber="775">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="774" pageNumber="775">
This species ranges from southwestern New Brunswick (Webster and Bousquet 2008: 22) to northeastern Iowa (Allamakee County, Doug A. Veal pers. comm. 2009), including the upper peninsula of Michigan (Casey 1920: 30, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1920" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Anchomenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="774" pageNumber="775" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inquisitor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="774" pageNumber="775">Anchomenus inquisitor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), south to west-central Illinois (Fulton County, Ken Karns pers. comm. 2009), southwestern Indiana (Blatchley 1910: 125), and west-central South Carolina (Ciegler 2000: 115).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
